WEBVTT

00:05.180 --> 00:07.060
- Hello.
- Hey, Rabbi.

00:07.060 --> 00:09.010
He's in his office,
you can go right in.

00:17.230 --> 00:19.060
- Rabbi.

00:19.060 --> 00:21.090
I just got off the phone
with the D.A.

00:21.090 --> 00:22.130
They're going
to be putting the girl's

00:22.130 --> 00:24.010
treating doctor up there.

00:24.010 --> 00:25.210
That's good news.
- It is.

00:25.210 --> 00:28.150
- It probably means there's
nothing conclusive he could say.

00:28.150 --> 00:30.170
It brings it down to her word
against yours.

00:30.170 --> 00:32.130
- I see.

00:32.130 --> 00:36.120
Eugene, would you mind
meeting with my board?

00:36.120 --> 00:38.180
- Your board?
- At the temple.

00:38.180 --> 00:40.190
They are paying the legal fees
and--

00:40.190 --> 00:42.070
- Why do they want to meet?

00:42.070 --> 00:43.210
- They'd like an assessment
of the case.

00:43.210 --> 00:46.200
They're no doubt
worried about damage control.

00:46.200 --> 00:50.070
If the synagogue's
rabbi is convicted of rape,

00:50.070 --> 00:52.070
I'm sure they'll want
to be prepared.

00:52.070 --> 00:54.110
- How do you feel
about me meeting with them?

00:54.110 --> 00:57.040
- I'm okay with it.
They've stuck by me, so--

01:01.160 --> 01:05.190
How are you assessing the case?

01:05.190 --> 01:08.030
- It's he said, she said, rabbi.

01:08.030 --> 01:11.030
You two were the only witnesses.

01:11.030 --> 01:12.230
You two and God.

01:15.130 --> 01:18.130
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:18.130 --> 01:26.110
♪ ♪

02:04.080 --> 02:06.030
- The likelihood is,
the girl will testify

02:06.030 --> 02:07.180
and then they'll rest.
I'll call you.

02:07.180 --> 02:09.050
After that, we close.

02:09.050 --> 02:12.000
This should be over
in a couple of days.

02:12.000 --> 02:13.100
I have to warn you,

02:13.100 --> 02:15.150
since this thing
is getting some publicity,

02:15.150 --> 02:17.170
the room will probably be full.

02:17.170 --> 02:19.220
You might want to convey
that to your congregation,

02:19.220 --> 02:22.120
because if they really plan
to turn out to support you,

02:22.120 --> 02:24.100
they better get there early.

02:24.100 --> 02:28.000
- I can't testify, Mr. Young.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.130
- Excuse me?

02:29.130 --> 02:36.020
- The truth here,
it could be very damning.

02:36.020 --> 02:38.100
- I thought you said
you were innocent.

02:38.100 --> 02:41.060
- I am.
I didn't rape her.

02:41.060 --> 02:46.180
But the sex--it may be--

02:46.180 --> 02:50.040
it was a little forcible.

02:50.040 --> 02:51.180
- Forcible?

02:51.180 --> 02:56.100
- It was consensual, but--

02:56.100 --> 02:57.120
- Forcible?

03:00.140 --> 03:02.190
Why don't you tell me
exactly what happened?

03:05.090 --> 03:09.170
- We had been having
a relationship

03:09.170 --> 03:13.090
and it was ending,
at her urging.

03:13.090 --> 03:15.100
It was the second time
she had come to my office

03:15.100 --> 03:17.160
for the purpose
of breaking it off.

03:17.160 --> 03:22.020
The first time
there were tears on both sides.

03:22.020 --> 03:25.100
And anger.

03:25.100 --> 03:29.080
We had an argument
which led, ultimately,

03:29.080 --> 03:32.210
to a rather passionate
session of lovemaking,

03:32.210 --> 03:37.010
followed by a mutual decision
to continue the relationship.

03:37.010 --> 03:39.020
That was the first time.

03:39.020 --> 03:42.050
This time, again,
she came to break it off,

03:42.050 --> 03:43.230
again we argued.

03:43.230 --> 03:46.170
And again,

03:46.170 --> 03:52.200
we began to kiss, fondle.

03:52.200 --> 03:57.060
At which point,
she reiterated it was wrong.

03:57.060 --> 04:00.050
But, Mr. Young,
she was the kind of person

04:00.050 --> 04:05.010
who liked sex more
when it was, well--

04:05.010 --> 04:07.160
And it was my belief,
the purpose of these breakups,

04:07.160 --> 04:10.120
it was to occasion my rage,

04:10.120 --> 04:13.000
because it excited her.

04:13.000 --> 04:18.000
The sex was
of a slightly forcible nature,

04:18.000 --> 04:20.070
even though
I remain absolutely convinced

04:20.070 --> 04:21.149
it was not only to her liking,

04:21.149 --> 04:24.040
but exactly what she wanted.

04:27.060 --> 04:29.050
- The jury
cannot hear that story.

04:29.050 --> 04:30.160
- Tell me about it.
- So he's guilty.

04:30.160 --> 04:31.230
Rabbi rapist.

04:31.230 --> 04:33.170
- In his mind,
he thinks she consented.

04:33.170 --> 04:35.020
- You know, there are thousands
and thousands

04:35.020 --> 04:36.110
of model rabbis out there.

04:36.110 --> 04:37.130
Why is it the ones
that come in here

04:37.130 --> 04:39.060
are all criminals?

04:39.060 --> 04:40.210
- Because we're criminal defense
attorneys, Ellenor.

04:40.210 --> 04:42.120
- Look, you haven't lost,
Eugene.

04:42.120 --> 04:44.080
Their case is only her word.

04:44.080 --> 04:46.150
You cross her good,
you've got reasonable doubt.

04:46.150 --> 04:48.070
- You want somebody
to second chair?

04:48.070 --> 04:50.090
- No.
Girl's 23.

04:50.090 --> 04:54.030
I don't want the jury to see
an army going against her.

04:54.030 --> 04:55.160
But the strategy's changed
a little.

04:55.160 --> 04:57.170
I could use some legwork.

04:57.170 --> 04:59.130
Chase down some old boyfriends.

04:59.130 --> 05:03.160
Jimmy?
- Whatever you need.

05:03.160 --> 05:05.130
- Thank you for meeting with us.

05:05.130 --> 05:06.140
- No problem.

05:06.140 --> 05:08.020
- Obviously, this matter

05:08.020 --> 05:10.080
is of significant concern
to the synagogue.

05:10.080 --> 05:13.070
And let me preface my remarks
by representing--

05:13.070 --> 05:15.110
- Enough with the preface.
The men works on an hourly.

05:15.110 --> 05:16.180
We pay for your prefaces.

05:16.180 --> 05:17.220
- Sam--
- Never mind.

05:17.220 --> 05:18.230
We're all busy people here.

05:18.230 --> 05:20.170
Say what you have to say.

05:20.170 --> 05:23.110
He's so damn worried all
the time about being delicate.

05:23.110 --> 05:24.190
Forgive me, rabbi.

05:24.190 --> 05:26.100
- It's all right, Sam.

05:26.100 --> 05:29.110
- Well, the fact of the matter
is, it is delicate.

05:29.110 --> 05:30.130
It goes without saying.

05:30.130 --> 05:32.020
The sordidness
of a trial

05:32.020 --> 05:34.130
would be very unfortunate
for this synagogue.

05:34.130 --> 05:36.100
We're anticipating a civil
suit as well.

05:36.100 --> 05:38.060
Since the event
in question

05:38.060 --> 05:40.010
took place
in the rabbi's office,

05:40.010 --> 05:41.160
she's already hired an attorney
who's made overtures.

05:41.160 --> 05:43.130
- The whole thing's a setup
for a civil suit.

05:43.130 --> 05:44.160
The girl is a liar.

05:44.160 --> 05:46.040
She's looking for money.

05:46.040 --> 05:47.230
As much
as we object on principle,

05:47.230 --> 05:50.110
we'll give it to her, so long
as it buys her silence.

05:50.110 --> 05:51.180
On the criminal suit as well.

05:51.180 --> 05:53.120
- You can't do that.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.020
- Technically no, of course not.

05:55.020 --> 05:56.140
But rape victims
change their minds

05:56.140 --> 05:58.010
about testifying all the time.

05:58.010 --> 06:00.070
- Why not just approach the girl
on your own?

06:00.070 --> 06:01.110
- Because I would assume

06:01.110 --> 06:03.020
that the threat
of cross-examination

06:03.020 --> 06:04.090
at the criminal trial

06:04.090 --> 06:05.220
would factor
into any negotiation.

06:05.220 --> 06:08.120
You are the only one
who can make that threat.

06:08.120 --> 06:10.070
- As well as make good on it.

06:10.070 --> 06:12.230
- What you're asking me
to do is illegal.

06:12.230 --> 06:20.190
- The legality
turns on the execution.

06:20.190 --> 06:22.010
- Let's cut to it.

06:22.010 --> 06:24.040
The man
is an enormously popular rabbi,

06:24.040 --> 06:25.130
central to our fundraising.

06:25.130 --> 06:27.110
We do not want that girl
telling her story

06:27.110 --> 06:30.100
in a courtroom
or any other public venue.

06:30.100 --> 06:33.080
We have a settlement fund.

06:33.080 --> 06:35.140
- I can't bribe a witness
in a criminal prosecution.

06:35.140 --> 06:37.130
- Don't be naive with me,
Mr. Young.

06:37.130 --> 06:39.180
You know exactly what you can
do, you know what you can't.

06:39.180 --> 06:41.040
You're the man's defense
attorney.

06:41.040 --> 06:43.010
You have a duty
to explore every option.

06:43.010 --> 06:44.170
- I don't like this one.
- Why?

06:44.170 --> 06:46.150
Where's your concern?

06:46.150 --> 06:48.110
If it lies with Rabbi Jacobs,

06:48.110 --> 06:51.060
you'll do it because it may
spare him criminal prosecution.

06:51.060 --> 06:52.110
If it lies with you,

06:52.110 --> 06:53.190
again,

06:53.190 --> 06:55.050
