28:15.160 --> 28:18.170
Because I thought,
"Who's ever gonna believe me?

28:18.170 --> 28:20.130
My word against his?"

28:20.130 --> 28:22.040
- Why didn't you think your word
would count for anything,

28:22.040 --> 28:23.100
Ms. Reynolds?

28:23.100 --> 28:24.150
Is there something wrong
with your word?

28:24.150 --> 28:26.060
- No, there isn't.

28:26.060 --> 28:27.230
- Did you ever go to a doctor
for an examination?

28:27.230 --> 28:29.060
- Yes.

28:29.060 --> 28:31.210
- He find any bruising
on your wrists?

28:31.210 --> 28:33.140
- No, but--
- He find any bruising

28:33.140 --> 28:36.030
on your thighs,
where my client supposedly

28:36.030 --> 28:39.080
pushed against you
with his knee?

28:39.080 --> 28:40.110
- No.

28:40.110 --> 28:43.000
I didn't have any bruises there.

28:43.000 --> 28:45.210
- Did you leave any marks
on Rabbi Jacobs?

28:45.210 --> 28:47.110
- Did I leave any marks?

28:47.110 --> 28:48.230
- Well, you had a hand free,
did you scratch him,

28:48.230 --> 28:50.110
or hit him, anything?

28:50.110 --> 28:51.210
- No.

28:51.210 --> 28:52.210
- You didn't do any
of those things?

28:52.210 --> 28:54.140
- I just tried to push him off.

28:54.140 --> 28:56.020
- Well, this wasn't a rape,
was it, Ms. Reynolds?

28:56.020 --> 28:57.170
- Yes, it was.
- You were angry at my client

28:57.170 --> 28:59.060
for refusing to consider
marrying you, weren't you?

28:59.060 --> 29:00.180
- As I said,
we fought some, but--

29:00.180 --> 29:02.120
- This is payback time,
isn't it, Ms. Reynolds?

29:02.120 --> 29:03.160
- What?
- Objection.

29:03.160 --> 29:04.230
- Have you hired
a civil attorney

29:04.230 --> 29:06.050
to sue both the rabbi
and the temple?

29:06.050 --> 29:07.160
- Objection.
- Goes to motive.

29:07.160 --> 29:09.140
- I'll allow it.

29:09.140 --> 29:10.220
- Is that your attorney
sitting right there,

29:10.220 --> 29:12.140
Ms. Reynolds?
- Yes.

29:12.140 --> 29:14.200
- He's representing you
in a lawsuit against the temple.

29:14.200 --> 29:16.070
- You know this isn't
about money.

29:16.070 --> 29:17.180
- Move to strike, nonresponsive.

29:17.180 --> 29:19.070
- Sustained.

29:19.070 --> 29:21.070
- Did you once date a man
named Michael Anderson?

29:21.070 --> 29:22.160
- Yes.

29:22.160 --> 29:24.060
- You ended that relationship?
- Yes.

29:24.060 --> 29:26.090
- Was one of the reasons
his lack of career ambition?

29:26.090 --> 29:27.210
- I told him that, yes, as in--

29:27.210 --> 29:29.110
- Thank you,
you answered the question.

29:29.110 --> 29:30.190
- There were a lot
of different reasons--

29:30.190 --> 29:33.230
- You answered the question.

29:33.230 --> 29:36.060
Is this a picture of you
in your high school yearbook?

29:36.060 --> 29:37.200
- Yes.

29:37.200 --> 29:41.010
- Could you read the caption
under "life goals"?

29:41.010 --> 29:42.170
- "To be rich,

29:42.170 --> 29:44.220
to be happy, to travel."

29:44.220 --> 29:47.130
- Do you have a friend
by the name of Susan Levine?

29:47.130 --> 29:48.200
- Yes.
- In fact,

29:48.200 --> 29:50.220
you told her
about your relationship

29:50.220 --> 29:53.020
with Rabbi Jacobs, didn't you?

29:53.020 --> 29:57.150
- Oh, I did tell her
at the very beginning, I forgot.

29:57.150 --> 29:58.210
It was under another context,

29:58.210 --> 30:00.080
it was when we first
started seeing--

30:00.080 --> 30:02.100
- So, you did tell somebody else
about it.

30:02.100 --> 30:04.220
That previous statement,
under oath, that was a lie.

30:04.220 --> 30:06.130
- It was a mistake.
- Got it.

30:06.130 --> 30:08.020
I guess mistakes happen.

30:08.020 --> 30:10.190
Is that the only mistake
so far in your testimony?

30:10.190 --> 30:11.220
- Yes.

30:11.220 --> 30:16.050
- Lucky I caught it, I guess.

30:16.050 --> 30:18.050
I'm done for now.

30:27.090 --> 30:29.180
- Ms. Reynolds,
when you went to the doctor,

30:29.180 --> 30:31.110
did he find any bruising?

30:31.110 --> 30:34.220
- Yes.
He found some vaginal bruising.

30:34.220 --> 30:36.220
- Thank you.

30:45.000 --> 30:47.000
- Did the doctor
find that bruising

30:47.000 --> 30:51.080
to be conclusive
of nonconsensual intercourse?

30:51.080 --> 30:52.200
- No.

30:52.200 --> 30:54.140
- Thank you.

31:01.010 --> 31:02.100
- Your Honor,
the Commonwealth

31:02.100 --> 31:03.210
would like to call
one more witness

31:03.210 --> 31:05.160
who is not on our list.

31:05.160 --> 31:07.050
- Objection.

31:15.040 --> 31:17.090
- Sheila Keenan.

31:17.090 --> 31:20.010
Three years ago she was raped
by Rabbi Jacobs.

31:20.010 --> 31:21.150
There was an out-of-court
settlement,

31:21.150 --> 31:24.130
coupled with an agreement
for her to keep silent.

31:24.130 --> 31:26.080
I would like
to call her to rehabilitate

31:26.080 --> 31:29.090
Ms. Reynolds' testimony.

31:29.090 --> 31:30.080
- Mr. Young.

31:34.010 --> 31:35.120
Mr. Young.

31:35.120 --> 31:37.030
- Uh...

31:37.030 --> 31:40.130
- Your Honor, a prior bad acts
in a criminal case,

31:40.130 --> 31:42.060
that's not even close
to being admissible.

31:42.060 --> 31:43.180
- I will be offering
to show pattern--

31:43.180 --> 31:45.040
- What pattern, two?

31:45.040 --> 31:46.220
Even if two made a pattern--
- May I finish?

31:46.220 --> 31:48.200
- We don't need
to hear you finish.

31:48.200 --> 31:50.180
That witness
would be so prejudicial, she--

31:50.180 --> 31:52.110
- I understand you don't like
this, but that does not mean--

31:52.110 --> 31:55.000
- I don't like it either,
Mr. Bullock.

31:55.000 --> 31:56.140
The only thing
we'd accomplish

31:56.140 --> 31:58.150
by bringing in that witness
is a guaranteed appeal.

31:58.150 --> 32:01.000
Even if you got a conviction,
it would just be overturned.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.160
- Not necessarily.

32:02.160 --> 32:04.060
If we limit the scope
of the questions, there's no--

32:04.060 --> 32:06.070
- Sorry, no chance.

32:06.070 --> 32:10.120
Is that it?

32:10.120 --> 32:11.120
Good.

32:11.120 --> 32:13.010
We close tomorrow afternoon.

32:21.140 --> 32:23.050
- You weren't going
to tell me that little detail?

32:23.050 --> 32:24.160
- Pursuant to the court
settlement,

32:24.160 --> 32:26.060
she's not allowed
to speak to anybody.

32:26.060 --> 32:27.150
- You were allowed to tell me.
You left that out.

32:27.150 --> 32:29.140
- I didn't rape her, either.

32:29.140 --> 32:31.010
Things just got out of control.

32:31.010 --> 32:33.050
- How much did you pay
this Keenan woman?

32:33.050 --> 32:34.110
- I'm not sure.

32:34.110 --> 32:36.130
- You're not sure?

32:36.130 --> 32:39.080
- The synagogue handled it.

32:39.080 --> 32:40.190
- Next on the agenda is--

32:40.190 --> 32:43.150
- I guess I am naive
after all, Mr. Lewis.

32:43.150 --> 32:45.010
I didn't think
it was board business

32:45.010 --> 32:46.100
to buy off rape victims.

32:46.100 --> 32:48.040
How deep does that fund go,
Mr. Lewis?

32:48.040 --> 32:50.020
- Now hold on--
- No, you hold on.

32:50.020 --> 32:51.150
I'm sure
he's a good rabbi,

32:51.150 --> 32:54.030
fills the seats,
generates a good cash flow,

32:54.030 --> 32:56.000
you get to use
the best wood for your pews,

32:56.000 --> 32:57.200
build the fanciest
temple in town,

32:57.200 --> 32:59.130
and when he commits
a crime or two,

32:59.130 --> 33:01.020
you can pay top dollar
to get him off,

33:01.020 --> 33:02.090
but here's what you don't know--

33:02.090 --> 33:04.170
- Mr. Young--
- Shh.

33:04.170 --> 33:07.010
I'm talking now.

33:07.010 --> 33:10.000
When it's me you hire,
you tell me the truth.

33:10.000 --> 33:12.050
You tell me everything
you think I might want to know.

33:12.050 --> 33:14.030
You hide facts for me, I quit.

33:14.030 --> 33:16.000
You got that?

33:16.000 --> 33:18.180
You understand me?

33:18.180 --> 33:21.140
- Are you finished?

33:21.140 --> 33:23.000
I'm an attorney, myself,
Mr. Young,

33:23.000 --> 33:24.210
so please don't lecture me.

33:24.210 --> 33:28.040
When you take on a case,
you take on a duty.

33:28.040 --> 33:29.190
You have no rights,
Mr. Young.

33:29.190 --> 33:32.070
The client has no obligation
to tell you everything.

33:32.070 --> 33:34.100
What he decides
to tell you is his choice alone.

33:34.100 --> 33:36.200
You take what he gives you,
and you make the best of it.

33:36.200 --> 33:38.040
We gave you your hand,
Mr. Young,

33:38.040 --> 33:39.180
you've played it very nicely.

33:39.180 --> 33:41.030
And don't barge
in here threatening to quit,

33:41.030 --> 33:42.220
because the judge
would never let you out.

33:42.220 --> 33:45.090
- I could quit just the same
and take the contempt finding.

33:45.090 --> 33:46.170
- It's not in your character
to quit.

33:49.140 --> 33:53.020
You don't think
we bothered to check you out?

33:53.020 --> 33:54.080
Now, please.

33:54.080 --> 33:56.090
Attend to your closing argument.

33:56.090 --> 33:57.180
From where I sit,

33:57.180 --> 33:59.040
this whole trial
comes down to summations,

33:59.040 --> 34:01.000
and I guarantee you

34:01.000 --> 34:02.190
Gavin Bullock is working on his.

34:12.219 --> 34:14.159
- You think you did good
in there, Counsel?

34:14.159 --> 34:15.230
You think you did good in there?

34:15.230 --> 34:17.080
- I asked you
to get away from me.

34:17.080 --> 34:18.170
- I won't be staying
away from you.

34:18.170 --> 34:20.040
Go in there
and give your closing now.

34:20.040 --> 34:21.139
- You want to take a shot at me?
- Yeah.

34:21.139 --> 34:23.020
I want to take it right now.
- Come on!

34:23.020 --> 34:24.199
- Eugene, Eugene, Eugene.
- Interrogate me!

34:24.199 --> 34:26.100
- For God's sake,
this isn't time

34:26.100 --> 34:27.230
for you to lose your focus.

34:27.230 --> 34:29.090
- What are you doing here?
- You got to go in there

34:29.090 --> 34:30.159
and hit a home run,
if you don't--

34:30.159 --> 34:31.179
- Are you checking up on me,
Jimmy?

34:31.179 --> 34:34.050
- Yeah, Eugene, I am.

34:34.050 --> 34:36.090
- You can tell Bobby I'm ready.

34:41.170 --> 34:43.110
- Mr. Young.

34:48.030 --> 34:50.040
- When this trial began,
I think a lot of people

34:50.040 --> 34:53.010
wanted to believe Terri Reynolds
for two reasons.

34:53.010 --> 34:56.179
First, it's become kind of
a pastime in this country

34:56.179 --> 34:59.040
to watch people fall
from high places.

34:59.040 --> 35:01.020
It's almost
as if it's a spectator sport

35:01.020 --> 35:02.150
as far as the media goes,

35:02.150 --> 35:06.090
and here, you have one
of the most respected rabbis

35:06.090 --> 35:07.170
in New England.

35:07.170 --> 35:09.110
A rabbi's rabbi, if you will.

35:09.110 --> 35:12.010
For him to be accused of rape,

35:12.010 --> 35:16.200
there's just something delicious
about that, isn't there?

35:16.200 --> 35:21.170
Second, there's something
so seemingly

35:21.170 --> 35:24.150
innocent about Terri Reynolds,
and good.

35:24.150 --> 35:27.040
And good people
don't make up lies like this.

35:27.040 --> 35:29.100
We all want to believe that.
I want to believe it.

35:29.100 --> 35:31.050
She could be your daughter,
your sister.

35:31.050 --> 35:34.010
She's just not going to make
something like this up.

35:34.010 --> 35:35.100
Well,
I'm not going to stand up here

35:35.100 --> 35:37.110
and tell you
I know Terri Reynolds.

35:37.110 --> 35:38.190
I don't.

35:38.190 --> 35:40.130
Neither does
the district attorney.

35:40.130 --> 35:41.170
He doesn't know her.

35:41.170 --> 35:43.080
Nor do any of you.

35:43.080 --> 35:46.150
All you get to do here
is weigh her credibility.

35:46.150 --> 35:48.160
And here's what the evidence
tells you about that,

35:48.160 --> 35:53.020
and by evidence,
I mean her very own testimony.

35:53.020 --> 35:54.100
She is a woman

35:54.100 --> 35:56.030
who admittedly wants
to be wealthy,

35:56.030 --> 35:57.230
going all the way
back to high school,

35:57.230 --> 36:00.220
when she listed
as a life goal to be rich.

36:00.220 --> 36:03.040
She's a woman
who wanted to marry my client,

36:03.040 --> 36:05.050
testified she was
angry with him.

36:05.050 --> 36:06.160
Well, one way
to punish him

36:06.160 --> 36:09.000
and to get rich
at the same time, cry rape.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.190
She's already got the civil
attorney in place.

36:11.190 --> 36:14.050
A criminal conviction here,

36:14.050 --> 36:17.080
that's money
in the bank, isn't it?

36:17.080 --> 36:19.180
The evidence
on her truthfulness:

36:19.180 --> 36:21.070
She's in love
with one man,

36:21.070 --> 36:22.200
but doesn't tell him,
"By the way,

36:22.200 --> 36:24.170
I'm seeing somebody else."

36:24.170 --> 36:27.130
She testified
that she didn't tell anybody

36:27.130 --> 36:30.080
about her relationship
with the Rabbi Jacobs, and then,

36:30.080 --> 36:32.230
when confronted about the truth
about telling her friend,

36:32.230 --> 36:34.210
she says, "Oh, yeah,
I forgot about that."

36:34.210 --> 36:36.160
Is she truthful?
I don't know.

36:36.160 --> 36:38.110
Like I said, I don't know her.

36:38.110 --> 36:42.130
Neither do any of you.

36:42.130 --> 36:45.140
What about the facts
of the case itself?

36:45.140 --> 36:48.130
She's being raped;
she doesn't scream.

36:48.130 --> 36:50.110
No screams, no bruises,

36:50.110 --> 36:52.210
no calling the police,
no fleeing the scene:

36:52.210 --> 36:54.160
does this sound
like a rape to you?

36:54.160 --> 36:56.070
Would she make it up after,

36:56.070 --> 36:58.150
as a scheme, just to get rich?

36:58.150 --> 37:00.120
I don't know.

37:00.120 --> 37:03.090
As I said, a part of us
wants to believe her,

37:03.090 --> 37:04.150
but when we examine the facts,

37:04.150 --> 37:05.150
can we?

37:05.150 --> 37:07.120
I don't know.

37:07.120 --> 37:09.100
I don't know her.

37:09.100 --> 37:10.190
In fact,

37:10.190 --> 37:12.160
if there's
one uncontroverted truth

37:12.160 --> 37:14.060
that we can be certain of,

37:14.060 --> 37:19.110
it's that none
of us here knows her.

37:19.110 --> 37:21.000
That we know.

37:24.060 --> 37:26.070
That,

37:26.070 --> 37:27.230
and that she wants to be rich.

37:41.120 --> 37:45.100
- It's not easy
being a rape victim these days.

37:45.100 --> 37:48.100
Because the trial system,

37:48.100 --> 37:52.000
it's no longer
about arriving at the truth.

37:52.000 --> 37:55.110
Believe it or not,
that used to be the idea.

37:55.110 --> 37:58.220
It's about winning and losing.

37:58.220 --> 38:00.090
Now, I'm here to win,
I admit it,

38:00.090 --> 38:03.130
and so is defense counsel.

38:03.130 --> 38:08.140
Winning means that if
you don't have the facts,

38:08.140 --> 38:10.210
you attack the one who does.

38:10.210 --> 38:12.110
This is
why Mr. Young

38:12.110 --> 38:15.080
has focused himself
on getting Terri Reynolds.

38:15.080 --> 38:19.080
He can't offer any testimonial
or physical evidence

38:19.080 --> 38:21.100
to dispute what she says,

38:21.100 --> 38:26.050
so he'll just get her.

38:26.050 --> 38:28.150
We're talking about a rape,
ladies and gentlemen,

38:28.150 --> 38:32.100
and he's dredging up
her high school yearbook.

38:32.100 --> 38:34.020
We're talking
about a man

38:34.020 --> 38:37.230
physically forcing himself
inside a young woman,

38:37.230 --> 38:42.010
and he's serving up
her career ambitions.

38:42.010 --> 38:43.160
He has no defense.

38:43.160 --> 38:46.050
He put on no defense.

38:46.050 --> 38:48.020
He chose, instead,

38:48.020 --> 38:50.150
to rape her again,
in this courtroom,

38:50.150 --> 38:53.120
and he's asked you
to be a part of it.

38:53.120 --> 38:55.160
Now, this has got to stop.

38:55.160 --> 38:58.090
She was raped,
for God's sake.

38:58.090 --> 39:00.190
He pinned her to the ground

39:00.190 --> 39:04.130
and performed a vile act
of violence against her.

39:04.130 --> 39:09.060
That is her testimony,
and it goes uncontradicted.

39:09.060 --> 39:11.080
You listened to her.

39:11.080 --> 39:14.040
Did she sound like a liar?

39:14.040 --> 39:20.050
Did she seem like someone
who was only looking for money?

39:20.050 --> 39:23.190
Defense counsel is right
about one thing.

39:23.190 --> 39:27.130
We offer only her word.

39:27.130 --> 39:29.210
But it's a good word,
ladies and gentlemen.

39:29.210 --> 39:32.200
They put up nothing
to contradict it

39:32.200 --> 39:37.100
because she was raped.

39:40.090 --> 39:41.070
It happened.

39:45.090 --> 39:51.070
How dare he put her on trial
in this room?

39:51.070 --> 39:53.130
Maybe the time has come
to put some of these kinds

39:53.130 --> 39:56.050
of defense tactics on trial.

40:08.090 --> 40:09.180
- Three times he did it, three.

40:09.180 --> 40:11.100
- I did no such thing.
- Oh, come on.

40:11.100 --> 40:13.220
He says we can't offer
testimonial evidence,

40:13.220 --> 40:16.040
he says the rapist gets
to sit quietly in his chair,

40:16.040 --> 40:17.220
he says we put on no defense.
- You didn't.

40:17.220 --> 40:20.000
- He was commenting
on the defendant not testifying,

40:20.000 --> 40:21.060
which he isn't allowed to do.

40:21.060 --> 40:22.170
- I am allowed
to say he put on--

40:22.170 --> 40:24.120
- The defendant has the right--
- All right.

40:24.120 --> 40:27.040
- It's grounds for a mistrial.
- You want a mistrial?

40:27.040 --> 40:29.100
- I want a stronger instruction
than the one you gave.

40:29.100 --> 40:30.130
- Come on.

40:30.130 --> 40:31.140
I gave an instruction.

40:31.140 --> 40:33.050
If I gave it any stronger,

40:33.050 --> 40:34.190
I'd have been
hanging out a flag.

40:34.190 --> 40:36.160
- Attacking me in your closing,
what the hell was that?

40:36.160 --> 40:37.230
What the hell
gives you the right to claim

40:37.230 --> 40:39.130
any moral superiority over me?

40:39.130 --> 40:41.100
Who gave you that?
- What are you talking about?

40:41.100 --> 40:43.040
- You know damn well
what I'm talking about.

40:43.040 --> 40:44.110
- Counsel.

40:44.110 --> 40:46.180
I think
you're overreacting here.

40:46.180 --> 40:48.170
Maybe you should take a walk
around the building,

40:48.170 --> 40:50.230
just to sort out what it is
that's got you this angry.

40:50.230 --> 40:52.150
- I know what got me this angry.

40:52.150 --> 40:54.130
He argued
that my client didn't testify.

40:54.130 --> 40:56.030
- He came close to doing that.

40:56.030 --> 40:58.030
I don't believe
he crossed the line.

40:58.030 --> 41:00.220
I believe I protected you
with an instruction.

41:00.220 --> 41:02.140
You made your objection
on the record,

41:02.140 --> 41:05.120
you preserved it for appeal.

41:05.120 --> 41:07.070
What else are you asking for?

41:07.070 --> 41:09.160
[knock at door]

41:09.160 --> 41:11.070
- Jury has a verdict.

41:30.220 --> 41:34.170
- Will the defendant
please rise.

41:34.170 --> 41:36.020
Madame Foreperson,

41:36.020 --> 41:37.130
you've reached
a unanimous verdict?

41:37.130 --> 41:39.070
- Yes, we have, Your Honor.

41:39.070 --> 41:41.210
- What say you?

41:41.210 --> 41:44.000
- In the matter
of the Commonwealth versus

41:44.000 --> 41:45.090
Richard Jacobs,

41:45.090 --> 41:47.130
on the charge
of aggravated rape,

41:47.130 --> 41:50.000
we find the defendant,

41:50.000 --> 41:53.080
Richard Jacobs, not guilty.

41:53.080 --> 41:54.210
- Oh, dear God.

42:04.180 --> 42:06.050
- Thank you, Mr. Young.

42:06.050 --> 42:07.130
Thank you.

42:07.130 --> 42:09.130
- Don't date, rabbi.

42:11.040 --> 42:13.220
- [screams]

